            "abstractNote": "The structure and composition of bat assemblages is mostly determined by features of the vegetation at local and landscape scales. We compared the bat assemblage present in a botanical garden with arti cial lakes and exotic plant species to that of the surrounding native forest, which we expected to di er. Over a year of sampling revealed that both habitats possess a predominance of medium-sized frugivorous bats, but of di erent species. More insectivorous bats were captured in the garden. Despite limited di erences in bat species composition, the structure of the two bat assemblages was noticeably di erent. These results indicate that bats respond di erently to available habitats even on a small scale.",
